      |       |    ======
      |       |        Makefile.am
      |       |        ...Test.cpp
      |       |        ...Test.h
      |       |        (possibly some data files)
      |       |
      |       |--- nonmem
      |            ======
      |                Makefile.am
      |                ...Test.cpp
      |                ...Test.h
      |                (possibly some data files)
      |
      |---  doc
           =====
              | Makefile.in
              | SpkCompiler.dox
              |
              |--- html
                   ====
                        (generated html, gif and other files)


<How To Build and Install SPK Compiler>

1. Assuming you're currently in the top level directory, "spkcompiler",
   run a shell script that generates the configure script.

   > ./autogen.sh

2. Run the generated configure script:

   > ./configure

3. If everything goes well, Makefiles should have been created in 
   subsequent subdirectories.  Change the directory and invoke "make"
   as follows:
   
   > cd spkcompiler
   > make

4. To install the libraries, you must become super-user:

   > su

   Then, type the following:

   > make install
   > exit

   This will install "spkcompiler" into /usr/local/bin/spktest/.

<How To Build/Run the Tests>

The unit tests require CppUnit.  If you do not have CppUnit installed on your machine, this is the time to do so.  You can find it at www.sourceforge.net and the installation procedure is posted in RFPK Software Group's internal website.

1. Move to the top directory and then to "tests".

2. Type:

   > make

3. Two sets of test are built in "tests/common" and "tests/nonmem" directories.
   Run "testall" in each directory.  

DONE.

